Package biscotti.collect

This package contains interfaces, implementations, and other utilities for working with Collections and Maps.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BoundedQueue<E>
    A capacity restricted Queue.
    Navigablelist<E>
    A Sortedlist augmented with navigation methods reporting closest matches for given search targets.
    SortedCollection<E>
    A Collection which maintains its elements in sorted order.
    Sortedlist<E>
    A SortedCollection which may contain duplicate elements and allows users to access and remove elements by their integer index.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ForwardingPeekingIterator<E>
    A PeekingIterator which forwards all its method calls to another PeekingIterator.
    Iterators2
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Iterators.
    Lists2
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Lists.
    Maps2
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Maps.
    Queues2
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Queues.
    RankList<E>
    A List optimized for efficient random access insertion and removal operations.
    Sets2
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Sets.
    Skiplist<E>
    A Sortedlist implementation based on a modified skip list.
    Skiplist.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of Skiplist instances.
    SkiplistSet<E>
    Note: This class should only be used for testing.
    Sortedlists
    Static utility methods which operate on or return Sortedlists.
    TreeBoundedQueue<E>
    An implementation of BoundedQueue backed by a TreeQueue.
    TreeBoundedQueue.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of TreeBoundedQueue instances.
    Treelist<E>
    A Sortedlist implementation, based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
    Treelist.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of Treelist instances.
    TreeQueue<E>
    An unbounded priority Queue based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
    TreeQueue.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of TreeQueue instances.
    TreeSet<E>
    Note: This class should only be used for testing.
    UnmodifiableListIterator<E>
    A ListIterator that does not support remove(), add(), and set(E).
    UnmodifiablePeekingIterator<E>
    A PeekingIterator that does not support remove().
